text.@value: This is the version of the letter published in “Letters of Edna St. Vincent Millay” edited by Allan Ross Macdougall who sent a letter to Sister Antonia in 1951, which was opened and responded to by the President Sister Antonine as Sister Antonia had died. She said she’d send a copy of the copy Sister Saint Helene had made of an original letter in her possession but they could not find any other letters of hers. Sister Ste Helene had either transcribed/copied this letter herself omitting some of it or Sister Antonine did when copying it to send to Macdougall.
